The paper deals with the concept of balancing sets in coding theory, which is closely related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves linear algebraic techniques, which are commonly used in computer science, particularly in the areas of data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the complexity of deciding whether a given set of vectors spans a balancing set, which is a problem in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
